results.name: Number of orderless same-trees of weight n with all leaves equal to 1.
comment: a(n) is also the number of orderless same-trees of weight n with all leaves greater than 1.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(1) = 1, a(n>1) = Sum_{d|n, d>1} binomial(a(n/d)+d-1, d).
program: (PARI) seq(n)={my(v=vector(n)); v[1]=1; for(n=2, n, v[n] = sumdiv(n, d, binomial(v[n/d]+d-1, d))); v} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Aug 20 2018
for n in range(2, 101): l+=[sum([binomial(l[n//d] + d - 1, d) for d in divisors(n)[1:]]), ]
